WEBVTT

0
00:00:00.209 --> 00:00:02.150
Healthy communities don't just happen,

1
00:00:02.329 --> 00:00:04.530
they're built through collaborative efforts to address

2
00:00:04.530 --> 00:00:07.210
the social factors that shape our well-being.

3
00:00:07.650 --> 00:00:12.050
These social determinants of health or SDLH include things like housing,

4
00:00:12.800 --> 00:00:13.170
education,

5
00:00:13.399 --> 00:00:14.350
social support,

6
00:00:14.409 --> 00:00:15.729
and access to health care.

7
00:00:16.520 --> 00:00:19.840
Addressing social determinants of health is essential for creating

8
00:00:19.840 --> 00:00:23.319
equitable opportunities for everyone to live healthier lives.

9
00:00:24.100 --> 00:00:26.180
That's why a multi-sector approach with

10
00:00:26.180 --> 00:00:28.809
collaboration between health care policy makers,

11
00:00:29.020 --> 00:00:32.119
community organizations and individuals is key.

12
00:00:32.779 --> 00:00:36.279
Some strategies for addressing social determinants of health include

13
00:00:36.900 --> 00:00:39.360
improving access to affordable housing,

14
00:00:39.779 --> 00:00:42.340
expanding access to quality education,

15
00:00:42.740 --> 00:00:44.919
strengthening social support networks,

16
00:00:45.419 --> 00:00:47.380
creating safe and healthy neighborhoods.

17
00:00:47.750 --> 00:00:50.470
And expanding access to affordable health care,

18
00:00:50.790 --> 00:00:52.930
health care professionals play a vital role

19
00:00:52.930 --> 00:00:55.250
in addressing social determinants of health,

20
00:00:55.509 --> 00:00:58.049
starting with screening patients for social needs

21
00:00:58.330 --> 00:01:00.860
by connecting patients to community resources and

22
00:01:00.860 --> 00:01:03.610
advocating for policies that address root causes,

23
00:01:03.709 --> 00:01:05.569
they can make a lasting impact.

24
00:01:05.940 --> 00:01:10.470
Building relationships with local organizations is also crucial as together we

25
00:01:10.470 --> 00:01:13.629
can tackle social determinants of health at the community level.

26
00:01:14.220 --> 00:01:18.080
Addressing social determinants of health is not just about health care,

27
00:01:18.180 --> 00:01:22.180
it's about creating a future where health disparities are a thing of the past.

28
00:01:22.540 --> 00:01:25.540
By working together we can build healthier communities

29
00:01:25.540 --> 00:01:28.470
and ensure everyone has the opportunity to thrive.